Sentencas: This paper reports on synthesis and evaluation of an intergrowth oxide, GdSrCoO4+delta (GSCO), as a new cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Evaluation of GdSrCoO4+δ intergrowth oxides as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The oxygen content and the thermal expansion coefficient of GSCO oxide powders were measured.
Titulo: Evaluation of GdSrCoO4+δ intergrowth oxides as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The GSCO oxide shows a semi-conducting behaviour in air with conductivities increasing from 16 S cm(-1) at 500 degrees C to 65 S cm(-1) at 800 degrees C.
Titulo: Evaluation of GdSrCoO4+δ intergrowth oxides as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The catalytic activities of GSCO oxides for oxygen reduction reactions are evaluated using symmetrical impregnated GdSrCoO4+delta-La0.9Sr0.1Ga0.8Mg0.2O3 (GSCO-LSGM) cathode fuel cells.
Titulo: Evaluation of GdSrCoO4+δ intergrowth oxides as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Titulo: Evaluation of GdSrCoO4+δ intergrowth oxides as cathode materials for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: C. Furthermore, thin LSGM electrolyte supported fuel cells with impregnated Ni anodes and GSCO cathodes exibit high power densities at reduced temperatures, e.g., 782 mW cm(-2) at 550 degrees C and 1314 mW cm(-2) at 650 degrees C, respectively.

Sentencas: These results demonstrate that GSCO is a promising cathode candidate for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells with LSGM electrolytes.
